oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Discharge certificate and service record of John Everett Siler
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Discharge certificate and service record for 1st Lt. John Everett Siler, Medical Corps, who sailed for France on Sept. 17 and arrived Sept. 23, 1918. He departed for home Nov. 18, 1918. He was discharged at St. Elizabeth's Hospital, Washington, D. C., on February 3, 1919 and was signed by Col. N. N. Miller, Medical Corps.
